                                                        <div class="def-block ddef_block " data-wl-senseid="ID_00020540_02">
                                                            <div class="def-head ddef_h">
                                                                <span class="def-info ddef-info epp-xref dxref B1">B1</span>
                                                                <div class="def ddef_d">Something that is missing cannot be <a class="query" href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/found" title="found">found</a> because it is not where it should be: </div>
                                                            </div>
                                                            <div class="def-body ddef_b">
                                                                <div class="examp dexamp eg">The <a class="query" href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/burglar" title="burglars" rel="">burglars</a> have been <a class="query" href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/arrest" title="arrested" rel="">arrested</a> but the <a class="query" href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/jewellery" title="jewellery" rel="">jewellery</a> is still missing.</div>
                                                                <div class="examp dexamp eg">When did you <a class="query" href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/realize" title="realize" rel="">realize</a> that the <a class="query" href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/money" title="money" rel="">money</a> was missing <span class="b db">from</span> <a class="query" href="https://cdo.demo.idm.fr/dictionary/english/your" title="your" rel="">your</a> <a class="query" href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/account" title="account" rel="">account</a>?</div>
