                                                                            <li class="had t-i"><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/thesaurus/absent">absent</a><span class="ti lml-5 example dexample">If you are absent from work for more than three days, you must provide a medical certificate.</span></li>
                                                                            <li class="had t-i"><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/thesaurus/awol">AWOL</a><span class="ti lml-5 example dexample">During the First World War soldiers who left their post were regularly charged with going AWOL.</span></li>
                                                                            <li class="had t-i"><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/thesaurus/go-awol">go AWOL</a><span class="ti lml-5 example dexample">My glasses have gone AWOL again.</span></li>
                                                                            <li class="had t-i"><a href="https://dictionary.cambridge.org/thesaurus/missing">missing</a><span class="ti lml-5 example dexample">Have you seen my credit card? It seems to be missing.</span></li>
